<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910607-0034</DOCNO><DOCID>910607-0034.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Republic Waste Industries Inc.:   Second-Quarter Net to Fall   Below Nine Cents a Share</HL><DATE>06/07/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   RWIN</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)POLLUTION CONTROL, WASTE MANAGEMENT SERVICES (POL)INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL SERVICES (SVC)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, REPURCHASES, SWAPS (BBK)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   Republic Waste Industries Inc., Houston, said it expectssecond-quarter net income to fall below the first quarter'snine cents a share, and will record a substantial charge inthe quarter for restructuring.   In the year-earlier quarter, the solid-waste-managementconcern had net income of $746,928, or 15 cents a share, onrevenue of $6.3 million. Results for the period have beenrestated to reflect the elimination of the effects of anacquisition.</LP><TEXT>   Republic Waste blamed lower second-quarter net onlower-than-expected volumes going into some landfills and theloss of some contracts. The company said it is taking stepsto reduce overhead, general administrative costs andoperating expenses, but didn't elaborate on the steps or theamount of the charge it will take in line with therestructuring.   It also said that an investment concern led by MichaelDeGroote would convert its $10 million debenture and exercisewarrants for four million shares of Republic Waste stocktoday, effectively gaining control of the company. Anagreement to acquire Alliance Holding Inc., Cleveland, in astock and debt-assumption package has been terminated, thecompany said.</TEXT></DOC>